Interface SParser

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    XDParseResult
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    StringParser

    public interface SParser
    Describes interface of source parsers.

      static char NOCHAR
      This value is used as the special "end of source" or "no character" value.

      • notChar

        char notChar(char ch)
        If character on actual position is not character specified by argument the method returns the actual character and sets position to next character. Otherwise it returns NOCHAR and actual position remains unchanged.
        Parameters:
        ch - Character to be checked.
        Returns:
        character on actual position or NOCHAR.

      • isInInterval

        char isInInterval(char minCh,
                  char maxCh)
        Check if actual position points to a character in given interval. Set the actual position to the next character if given character was in the specified interval.
        Parameters:
        minCh - minimum of checked interval.
        maxCh - maximum of checked interval.
        Returns:
        the actual character character from actual position, otherwise return NOCHAR.

      • notInInterval

        char notInInterval(char minCh,
                   char maxCh)
        Check if actual position points to a character out of given interval. Set the actual position to the next character if given character was recognized.
        Parameters:
        minCh - minimum of checked interval.
        maxCh - maximum of checked interval.
        Returns:
        the actual character character from actual position, otherwise return NOCHAR.

        Returns:

        Returns:

      • isOneOfTokens

        int isOneOfTokens(java.lang.String... tokens)
        If on source position is one of tokens specified in the argument the * method returns index to this item and sets position to the next position after a token. Otherwise it returns -1.
        Parameters:
        tokens - Array of tokens be checked.
        Returns:
        Index of found token or -1.

      • findToken

        boolean findToken(java.lang.String token)
        Find token. If the token was found returns true and sets position to the position of token. Otherwise returns false and sets position to the end of source.
        Parameters:
        token - Token to be found.
        Returns:
        true if the token was found.

      • findChar

        boolean findChar(char ch)
        Skip to specified character. The position is set to the found character. Returns true and sets position to the position of character. Otherwise returns false and sets position to the end of source.
        Parameters:
        ch - Character to be searched for.
        Returns:
        true if the character was found.

      • findOneOfChars

        char findOneOfChars(java.lang.String chars)
        Skip to first occurrence of one of specified character set. The position is set to the found character.Return a character from the list of characters if the character was found, otherwise return NOCHAR and set the position to the end of source.
        Parameters:
        chars - String with set of characters.
        Returns:
        found character or NOCHAR.
